data.title: The New York Times
data.text:
Morning

Frank Sinatra and Jacqueline Bisset star in the 1968 film “The Detective” at 11 : 30 P.M. on Channel 7.

12:30 P.M. (4) — N.F.L. Football: Jets vs. Miami Dolphins. (3 hrs.)

1:30 P.M. (2) — 30 Minutes: A profile of a boxer; reports on teen‐age suicide, topics. (R) (30 mins.).

4 P.M. (2) — N.F.L. Football: Green Bay Packers vs. Detroit Lions. (2 hrs., 45 rains.)

6:30 P.M. (13) — Camera Three: A visit with Tatyana Grosman, the artist who founded Universal Limited Art Editions, a litography workshop. (1 hr.)

9 P.M. (2) — The Gift Starring Glenn Ford, Gary Frank, and Julie Harris. A man returns to his boyhood home of Brooklyn on Christmas leave from the Navy. (2 hrs.)

9 P.M. (13) — Bar Mitzvah Boy: A story about the conflicts a young boy encounters prior to the religious ceremony celebrating a boy's transition into manhood. (2 hrs.)

Afternoon
